Recall that the second order Taylor polynomial of a function $p(q)$ at a
point $q = a$ is given by $T_{20}(x)$ where,

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle T_{20}(q) = p(a) + p'(a)(q - a) + \frac{1}{2}p''(a)(q-a)^{2} + .. + \frac{1}{20!}p^{(20)}(a)(q-a)^{20}
\end{align*}

In our case, $a=1$ and $p(q) = e^{3q}$.

However even knowing this, it might not be clear how to proceed - Look
at what $a_{20}$ is in the equation above and try to figure out a
pattern to help you compute this value.

